/*
:name: mod_comp
:type: equiv
:verilog_top: mod_comp.foo
:pyrope_top: mod_comp.foo
*/

// `a % b` where the dividend is a COMPUTED value (not an input port), so its
// non-negativity comes from the result pin's unsigned stamp and its range from
// the bitwidth pass (bw_meta) rather than the io_meta declared envelope — a
// distinct path in tolg lower_mod. Covers the power-of-two and `% 3` lowerings
// over a sum/xor dividend. lgcheck proves it bit-exact against native `%`.
comb foo(a:u8, b:u8) -> (rp2:u4, r3:u2) {
  rp2 = (a + b) % 8
  r3  = (a ^ b) % 3
}
